3
00:00:29.360 --> 00:00:31.719
All you had to do was
pick up the phone and tell us

4
00:00:31.720 --> 00:00:34.159
you were still breathing.
I didn't even know you were alive.

5
00:00:34.160 --> 00:00:37.319
The money. the gangs.
I'm taking it all back.

6
00:00:39.760 --> 00:00:41.719
Thought I'd be
higher up your kill list.

7
00:00:41.720 --> 00:00:43.319
You and I want the same thing.

8
00:00:43.320 --> 00:00:46.799
So. either help me or fuck off.

9
00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:48.519
Go on then...

10
00:00:48.520 --> 00:00:50.679
The Wallaces
stood on our shoulders

11
00:00:50.680 --> 00:00:52.879
and wanted our thanks for it.
They used you. Dad.

12
00:00:52.880 --> 00:00:54.959
For years. but not anymore.

13
00:00:57.080 --> 00:00:58.799
London belongs to us now.

14
00:00:58.800 --> 00:01:00.759
We're offering you a piece of it.

15
00:01:00.760 --> 00:01:03.759
I will not work with a man
who helped kill my son.

16
00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:06.119
If you want what you claim.
you must be prepared to do

17
00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:08.119
everything without fear.
without care.

18
00:01:08.120 --> 00:01:10.000
I'm sorry.

19
00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:14.559
I will not fight for a London
where Sean comes out on top.

20
00:01:14.560 --> 00:01:17.439
Sean won't be at the top. We will.

21
00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:19.519
You wish he'd never
come back at all.

22
00:01:19.520 --> 00:01:22.639
They killed my dad! Sean did this.

23
00:01:22.640 --> 00:01:24.479
I know how you can get to Sean.

24
00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:28.639
Don't lie to me. Mum.
What did you do?

25
00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:33.999
It's power or family.
You can't have both...

26
00:01:39.880 --> 00:01:42.199
I'm gonna make you watch.
Sean Wallace.

27
00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:45.319
I'm gonna take
everything you ever built.

28
00:01:45.320 --> 00:01:47.519
Your power...

29
00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:48.759
Your people...

30
00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:50.840
And I'm gonna replace you.

31
00:02:31.960 --> 00:02:34.519
Yep... Come on.

32
00:02:59.960 --> 00:03:03.200
Yippee!

33
00:03:25.280 --> 00:03:27.640
Are you OK. Mummy?
Yeah. of course...

34
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:35.280
Mum?

35
00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:00.200
Mum?

36
00:04:01.760 --> 00:04:03.479
Faster.

37
00:04:03.480 --> 00:04:05.960
Faster! Fucking faster!
Faster! Faster!

38
00:04:06.880 --> 00:04:08.480
Car! Car! Car! Car!

39
00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:25.600
Stop the car!

40
00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:29.119
Stop the fucking car now!
I'm warning you!

41
00:04:29.120 --> 00:04:31.319
Oh. God... Pull over!

42
00:04:31.320 --> 00:04:32.960
Ram this bitch off the road.

43
00:04:35.080 --> 00:04:37.600
It's OK. Samuel.

44
00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:42.159
Hold on! Samuel. hold on.

45
00:04:42.160 --> 00:04:44.799
I'm warning you... Fuck this!

46
00:04:44.800 --> 00:04:46.479
Closer!

47
00:04:46.480 --> 00:04:48.960
Mum!

48
00:04:50.120 --> 00:04:51.359
Mum!

49
00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:52.920
Samuel. hold on!

50
00:04:53.640 --> 00:04:55.679
Keep your head down Samuel!

51
00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:57.799
Mum!

52
00:04:57.800 --> 00:04:59.480
Mum!

53
00:05:00.320 --> 00:05:02.919
Hit her!

54
00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:39.280
Are they coming back. Mummy?

55
00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:43.480
They're gone. It's OK.

56
00:05:55.920 --> 00:05:59.079
The person you are
calling is unable to take your call.

57
00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:28.759
Help me...

58
00:06:38.040 --> 00:06:41.439
Help me. Please help me.

59
00:06:41.440 --> 00:06:42.879
Please. Please.

60
00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:46.879
Pl-Please.

61
00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:52.520
Please...

62
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.040
Samuel...

63
00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:01.760
M-Mum?

64
00:07:03.400 --> 00:07:05.360
I'm so sorry.

65
00:08:11.880 --> 00:08:13.840
Hey. guys.

66
00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:38.160
- All good?
- Yeah. This is yours.

67
00:08:39.680 --> 00:08:41.600
Faz? Yo...

68
00:08:42.640 --> 00:08:45.119
So. what was the delay?

69
00:08:45.120 --> 00:08:47.839
Driver said there was
traffic at the port.

70
00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:50.759
But it's here now. anyway.
And half's already gone out.

71
00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:52.400
It's all good.

72
00:09:40.400 --> 00:09:42.440
I'll shift these now.
See you in a bit.

73
00:09:57.840 --> 00:10:00.280
Sorry I'm late.
Yeah. well. they're here already.

74
00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:02.840
Come on...

75
00:10:19.520 --> 00:10:22.279
So... you're the "cop"?

76
00:10:22.280 --> 00:10:25.680
Ex-cop.

77
00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:34.560
How does that work?

78
00:10:35.360 --> 00:10:37.879
Seems like a big change of mind.

79
00:10:37.880 --> 00:10:40.960
Do you really think we'd be working
with Elliot if we had any doubts?

80
00:10:41.760 --> 00:10:44.680
We're supplying all of London.
No one's complaining.

81
00:10:51.520 --> 00:10:53.239
Listen. I don't speak Korean.

82
00:10:53.240 --> 00:10:56.880
and if you don't wanna do business.
then you're welcome to leave.

83
00:11:01.160 --> 00:11:03.719
OK. OK.

84
00:11:03.720 --> 00:11:06.159
What is your rate?
Nineteen and a half.

85
00:11:06.160 --> 00:11:08.639
That's more than we're paying now.

86
00:11:08.640 --> 00:11:10.479
Cos you're paying for shit.

87
00:11:10.480 --> 00:11:12.319
I guarantee 80% purity.

88
00:11:12.320 --> 00:11:15.079
Now I know you're lying.

89
00:11:15.080 --> 00:11:18.599
Well. if you don't believe me-
Woah. woah. woah...

90
00:11:18.600 --> 00:11:20.040
Take it easy.

91
00:11:28.680 --> 00:11:32.080
Quantity's not a problem.
We can get you as much as you need.

92
00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:41.920
Mm...

93
00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:41.839
Boss? Boss?

94
00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:43.639
What the fuck have you done?
Don't move!

95
00:12:43.640 --> 00:12:46.119
I know what it looks like.
but you're wrong.

96
00:12:46.120 --> 00:12:47.960
Everyone just calm down!

97
00:12:53.160 --> 00:12:54.920
Don't fucking tempt me.

98
00:12:56.640 --> 00:12:58.279
Listen. Be easy.

99
00:12:58.280 --> 00:13:00.879
I don't know what's happened
to your boss. but that's not us. OK?

100
00:13:00.880 --> 00:13:03.720
Elliot?
Elliot. you need to see this.

101
00:13:07.760 --> 00:13:10.160
Shannon. go! Go!

102
00:13:20.440 --> 00:13:22.240
What's going on?

103
00:13:27.520 --> 00:13:29.040
Hey. hey. are you alright?

104
00:13:32.040 --> 00:13:35.400
Jesus Christ.
Somebody help her up...

105
00:13:45.960 --> 00:13:47.440
Are you alright?

106
00:13:51.400 --> 00:13:53.000
This is weird.

107
00:14:29.760 --> 00:14:31.600
Good evening. Liam. Mrs Wallace.

108
00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:55.000
Aw.

109
00:15:31.040 --> 00:15:32.680
I appreciate you coming here.

110
00:15:44.040 --> 00:15:45.599
People are worried. Marian.

111
00:15:45.600 --> 00:15:47.679
Sean's due in court this week

112
00:15:47.680 --> 00:15:51.399
and there is all kind of
different stories going around.

113
00:15:51.400 --> 00:15:53.679
They are saying that...

114
00:15:53.680 --> 00:15:56.119
he's going to turn some of us in...

115
00:15:56.120 --> 00:15:58.279
in exchange for a lighter sentence.

116
00:15:58.280 --> 00:16:01.160
You know as much about
Sean's intentions as I do.

117
00:16:04.040 --> 00:16:05.840
He knows a lot about my business.

118
00:16:08.440 --> 00:16:11.439
About all of us. no?
Hm. Including me.

119
00:16:11.440 --> 00:16:14.240
You're different. you're his family.

120
00:16:20.440 --> 00:16:22.959
I don't know what
you want me to say. Luan.

121
00:16:22.960 --> 00:16:25.279
Something reassuring.

122
00:16:25.280 --> 00:16:28.119
I haven't spoken to Sean
since he was arrested.

123
00:16:28.120 --> 00:16:30.640
I have no idea what
he's planning to do...

124
00:16:33.240 --> 00:16:35.319
It's your turn!

125
00:16:35.320 --> 00:16:37.840
Oh... Oh-ho!

126
00:16:39.560 --> 00:16:41.359
I...

127
00:16:41.360 --> 00:16:43.159
got you a present. Elly.

128
00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:12.439
Maybe you can
go and visit him. or...

129
00:17:12.440 --> 00:17:15.079
make sure he doesn't betray us.
Marian...

130
00:17:15.080 --> 00:17:16.439
No.

131
00:17:16.440 --> 00:17:19.039
Well this is in
everyone's interest. no?

132
00:17:19.040 --> 00:17:20.560
I said no.

133
00:17:26.720 --> 00:17:28.239
We're about to do the cake.

134
00:17:28.240 --> 00:17:30.319
Just one minute. please. No.

135
00:17:30.320 --> 00:17:32.599
We agreed. "no work tonight".
One minute.

136
00:17:32.600 --> 00:17:36.599
I'm coming. please.
Daddy! Mum. It's Elly...

137
00:17:36.600 --> 00:17:40.120
Elly...

138
00:17:48.640 --> 00:17:51.200
What happened?
She just collapsed.

139
00:17:55.360 --> 00:17:56.880
Did she take something?

140
00:19:14.680 --> 00:19:16.920
Simone?

141
00:19:18.560 --> 00:19:20.039
Simone?

142
00:19:20.040 --> 00:19:21.680
OK. OK. I'm coming!

143
00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:31.680
What?

144
00:19:33.120 --> 00:19:36.639
Look it's. um. quite hard to give
any accurate numbers at the moment

145
00:19:36.640 --> 00:19:38.759
because it's coming in
from hospitals.

146
00:19:38.760 --> 00:19:41.239
police. boroughs all over London.

147
00:19:41.240 --> 00:19:43.239
It's a developing situation.

148
00:19:43.240 --> 00:19:46.999
What we can say for sure
is that so far we have

149
00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:50.559
over 300 fatalities.
but that figure's bound to rise.

150
00:19:50.560 --> 00:19:52.639
I'm sorry. this is all from cocaine?

151
00:19:52.640 --> 00:19:55.360
Yeah. Apparently.
there was a poisoned batch.

152
00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:02.720
Are you ready for this?

153
00:20:08.520 --> 00:20:11.320
Mayor. over here! Mayor!

154
00:20:16.440 --> 00:20:19.279
Before I address any questions...

155
00:20:19.280 --> 00:20:22.479
I would like to say that
my thoughts and my prayers

156
00:20:22.480 --> 00:20:24.799
are with the victims
of tonight's events.

157
00:20:24.800 --> 00:20:26.960
And this is a tragedy for them...

158
00:20:27.680 --> 00:20:30.719
for their families
and for their loved ones...

159
00:20:30.720 --> 00:20:32.760
But it's also a tragedy for London.

160
00:20:34.080 --> 00:20:37.440
And one that has been coming
for a long time.

161
00:20:38.280 --> 00:20:40.799
And there is no doubt
in my mind that the blame

162
00:20:40.800 --> 00:20:46.079
for all of this lies squarely at
the feet of the criminal gangs.

163
00:20:46.080 --> 00:20:49.159
See. this is what happens
when organised crime gangs

164
00:20:49.160 --> 00:20:54.599
are allowed to prosper
without fear of consequence.

165
00:20:54.600 --> 00:20:58.159
Well. no more.
I promise you that I will use

166
00:20:58.160 --> 00:21:03.559
every single resource available
to me to rid London of these gangs.

167
00:21:15.240 --> 00:21:17.160
Well?

168
00:21:23.600 --> 00:21:25.200
Shit...

169
00:21:29.120 --> 00:21:31.519
It's happening all over London.
Do we know what caused this?

170
00:21:31.520 --> 00:21:34.879
Fentanyl. There are high traces
of it in everything we've tested.

171
00:21:34.880 --> 00:21:36.719
Is this a fuck up our end? No.

172
00:21:36.720 --> 00:21:38.759
It's even in packages
we hadn't opened yet.

173
00:21:38.760 --> 00:21:40.759
Well. it has to be
the Bolivians then.

174
00:21:40.760 --> 00:21:44.919
- They're adamant it was clean when.
- It left them. - Do we trust them?

175
00:21:44.920 --> 00:21:48.039
Well. someone's done this
deliberately to fuck us up!

176
00:21:48.040 --> 00:21:51.119
Yeah. but who though?
Marian. Luan. the Kurds...

177
00:21:51.120 --> 00:21:53.239
If you wanted to move against us.

178
00:21:53.240 --> 00:21:55.120
you'd weaken us first. like this.

179
00:21:56.160 --> 00:21:57.880
Our associates want a meeting.

180
00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:02.080
Saba!

181
00:22:04.080 --> 00:22:06.439
Call Faz. tell him
I need to speak to the driver

182
00:22:06.440 --> 00:22:09.280
who brought in tonight's shipment.
Yeah. Got you.

183
00:23:26.640 --> 00:23:27.999
It's your product.

184
00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:31.239
You're responsible for
what happened. No excuses.

185
00:23:31.240 --> 00:23:34.559
Everyone will be reimbursed
for what they bought.

186
00:23:34.560 --> 00:23:37.479
It's not just about
the money for this shipment.

187
00:23:37.480 --> 00:23:40.359
You heard the fucking Mayor.
The police will make our lives hell

188
00:23:40.360 --> 00:23:43.079
for what happened.
This is bad news for us too.

189
00:23:43.080 --> 00:23:44.679
I don't care. It's your fuck up.

190
00:23:44.680 --> 00:23:48.599
It's not a fuck up.
What would you call it?

191
00:23:48.600 --> 00:23:50.200
An attack.

192
00:23:51.520 --> 00:23:54.079
There was fentanyl in that
whole shipment. even packages

193
00:23:54.080 --> 00:23:55.679
we hadn't even opened yet.

194
00:23:55.680 --> 00:23:57.840
That cocaine was
deliberately spiked.

195
00:24:00.560 --> 00:24:01.920
By who?

196
00:24:07.240 --> 00:24:09.160
That's what I intend to find out.

197
00:24:10.360 --> 00:24:11.960
And when you do...

198
00:24:14.600 --> 00:24:17.520
I want them handed over to me.

199
00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:21.119
Let's find them first. No.

200
00:24:23.200 --> 00:24:24.840
I'm gonna make them pay...

201
00:24:26.080 --> 00:24:28.839
and anyone who tries
to stop me too.

202
00:24:35.720 --> 00:24:37.320
I need to take this.

203
00:24:47.000 --> 00:24:48.679
Yeah...

204
00:24:48.680 --> 00:24:50.759
I'm at the driver's place. Yeah?

205
00:24:50.760 --> 00:24:53.519
The men I sent. they're all dead.
OK. Don't touch anything.

206
00:24:53.520 --> 00:24:55.679
I'll be right over.
Alright. cool.

207
00:25:03.760 --> 00:25:05.679
Over where? Nowhere.

208
00:25:05.680 --> 00:25:07.640
It's just business.

209
00:25:14.760 --> 00:25:17.960
If your child
had been killed tonight...

210
00:25:18.800 --> 00:25:20.919
would you allow
yourself to be fobbed off with

211
00:25:20.920 --> 00:25:23.720
a fucking bullshit excuse like that?

212
00:25:25.040 --> 00:25:26.240
No.

213
00:25:32.680 --> 00:25:34.440
Let's go then.

214
00:25:50.760 --> 00:25:52.360
You were very quiet in there.

215
00:25:54.320 --> 00:25:56.319
Those drugs
didn't come through my ports.

216
00:25:56.320 --> 00:25:58.039
so this has nothing to do with me.

217
00:25:58.040 --> 00:26:01.239
That's because you wouldn't
let us use your ports.

218
00:26:01.240 --> 00:26:04.120
I don't do business
with police officers.

219
00:26:05.480 --> 00:26:07.080
Neither should you.

220
00:26:57.360 --> 00:26:58.960
Yo.

221
00:27:18.520 --> 00:27:20.840
Yo. Make sure
the door's locked. yeah?

222
00:27:21.600 --> 00:27:23.520
Let me know if you find anything.

223
00:27:38.960 --> 00:27:42.160
- That's the guy that drove.
- The shipment? - Yeah. that's him.

224
00:27:45.160 --> 00:27:47.400
You find his phone?
No. It's gone.

225
00:27:48.640 --> 00:27:50.840
Must have been taken
when he was killed.

226
00:27:51.760 --> 00:27:53.360
Here. Come. through here.

227
00:27:57.240 --> 00:27:58.840
Look...

228
00:28:02.480 --> 00:28:04.799
Who the fuck is that?
That's all we have of him here.

229
00:28:04.800 --> 00:28:06.320
Run it forward.

230
00:28:09.880 --> 00:28:11.800
Yo. yo. Stop there.

231
00:28:19.240 --> 00:28:21.880
What the fuck?!

232
00:28:52.200 --> 00:28:54.680
Run it back. Yeah?

233
00:28:59.480 --> 00:29:01.360
Slowly. fuck's sake.

234
00:29:07.760 --> 00:29:09.680
Stop.

235
00:29:43.960 --> 00:29:46.799
On no. don't bother. Right.

236
00:29:46.800 --> 00:29:48.560
Uh...

237
00:29:50.040 --> 00:29:51.879
So. where are we with this?

238
00:29:51.880 --> 00:29:54.239
At the moment we're managing
a crisis situation

239
00:29:54.240 --> 00:29:57.359
and trying to get the message out
about the dangers of cocaine use-

240
00:29:57.360 --> 00:29:59.320
OK. yes. I understand that. but...

241
00:30:00.120 --> 00:30:04.160
What are we doing to catch the people
who are responsible for this?

242
00:30:07.800 --> 00:30:10.959
This is the man we believe brought
this cocaine into the country.

243
00:30:10.960 --> 00:30:12.759
His name is Elliot Carter.

244
00:30:12.760 --> 00:30:15.200
He's an ex-undercover police
officer.

245
00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:19.320
You are fucking joking?

246
00:30:22.360 --> 00:30:24.400
Why isn't this guy locked up already?

247
00:30:25.920 --> 00:30:28.639
Knowing who did it and proving it
are two different things.

248
00:30:28.640 --> 00:30:32.479
OK. I want this guy
to be our number one target.

249
00:30:32.480 --> 00:30:34.880
We find the evidence
and lock him the fuck up.

250
00:30:38.040 --> 00:30:41.479
Listen. You two. do either
of you recognise this man?

251
00:30:41.480 --> 00:30:43.599
I-I don't know. No. boss.

252
00:30:43.600 --> 00:30:45.719
Look. take this photo
and spread the word.

253
00:30:45.720 --> 00:30:47.360
I want him fucking found.

254
00:30:48.120 --> 00:30:49.200
Go!

255
00:30:50.720 --> 00:30:52.599
- Faz.
- Yo. You got the keys to the truck?

256
00:30:52.600 --> 00:30:54.239
Yeah. Yeah.

257
00:31:03.800 --> 00:31:05.999
After the driver got off the ferry.
he didn't come

258
00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:10.439
straight to the factory.
He took a detour. and stopped here.

259
00:31:10.440 --> 00:31:12.519
Stopped for 30 minutes.

260
00:31:12.520 --> 00:31:16.080
Thirty minutes isn't long enough
to spike that much coke. man.

261
00:31:16.960 --> 00:31:18.440
No.

262
00:31:20.240 --> 00:31:22.919
But it is enough time
to swap the original shipment

263
00:31:22.920 --> 00:31:24.679
with one already
laced with fentanyl.

264
00:31:27.480 --> 00:31:28.959
So. what is this then?

265
00:31:28.960 --> 00:31:31.000
That's what we're about to find out.

266
00:32:02.360 --> 00:32:03.960
Luan. wait!

267
00:32:22.400 --> 00:32:23.440
Hold on!

268
00:32:24.640 --> 00:32:26.240
Jesus.

269
00:33:17.320 --> 00:33:18.800
You boys is trespassing.

270
00:33:19.520 --> 00:33:20.919
We just want a quiet word.

271
00:33:20.920 --> 00:33:23.360
Not that quiet
if you're bringing guns.

272
00:33:24.520 --> 00:33:26.120
What do youse want?

273
00:33:28.760 --> 00:33:32.639
A truck stopped here earlier
tonight. wanted to ask why.

274
00:33:32.640 --> 00:33:35.839
I don't know nothing about no truck.

275
00:33:35.840 --> 00:33:37.520
- Do you see a truck?
- Nope.

276
00:33:38.400 --> 00:33:40.039
Hm?

277
00:33:40.040 --> 00:33:42.119
Must be mistaken. No mistake.

278
00:33:42.120 --> 00:33:44.239
It was on the satnav.
Ah maybe you should speak

279
00:33:44.240 --> 00:33:46.560
to the driver then. He is dead.

280
00:33:47.440 --> 00:33:49.440
Well. that's unfortunate.

281
00:33:51.520 --> 00:33:53.360
Do you think this is a fucking joke?

282
00:33:56.040 --> 00:33:58.919
Test me. Come on.

283
00:33:58.920 --> 00:34:00.840
Test me. Maybe...

284
00:34:01.560 --> 00:34:03.919
we should just calm down.

285
00:34:03.920 --> 00:34:09.759
No. You two should fuck off out of
here now while you still have time.

286
00:34:09.760 --> 00:34:11.399
I have a picture of a man...

287
00:34:11.400 --> 00:34:13.519
just want to see
if any of you recognise him.

288
00:34:13.520 --> 00:34:16.519
You heard him. Go fuck yourself.

289
00:34:16.520 --> 00:34:18.960
You fucking bastard!

290
00:34:19.880 --> 00:34:21.919
Come on!

291
00:34:21.920 --> 00:34:24.199
Get those fuckers!

292
00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:50.520
Fuck...

293
00:36:57.600 --> 00:36:58.959
Fuck!

294
00:38:03.000 --> 00:38:04.600
Shit...

295
00:38:24.480 --> 00:38:27.200
Cornelius Quinn.
that name mean anything to you?

296
00:38:43.160 --> 00:38:44.800
Phone.

297
00:38:49.800 --> 00:38:51.280
There's only one number.

298
00:38:52.040 --> 00:38:53.080
Call it.

299
00:39:05.680 --> 00:39:07.279
Cornelius.

300
00:39:11.480 --> 00:39:13.040
Sean?

301
00:39:13.920 --> 00:39:15.520
Did you fucking do this?

302
00:39:16.480 --> 00:39:18.679
I asked you a fucking question!

303
00:39:18.680 --> 00:39:20.879
Did you send that man
to poison those drugs. cos-

304
00:39:23.400 --> 00:39:25.120
Sean Wallace.

305
00:40:20.560 --> 00:40:23.240
You OK? Right as fucking rain.

306
00:40:24.560 --> 00:40:26.480
We're still going ahead with this?

307
00:40:27.200 --> 00:40:28.800
Oh. yeah.

308
00:40:33.280 --> 00:40:34.880
Mrs Wallace... Mm-hm?

309
00:40:36.160 --> 00:40:38.080
Ed Dumani is here.
He wants to see you.

310
00:40:51.560 --> 00:40:54.439
I'd have thought you'd be
too busy cleaning up your mess

311
00:40:54.440 --> 00:40:56.680
to make house calls
at this time of day.

312
00:40:58.960 --> 00:41:00.960
Last night's spiking...

313
00:41:02.640 --> 00:41:04.839
it wasn't Elliot.

314
00:41:04.840 --> 00:41:06.559
It was Sean's doing.

315
00:41:06.560 --> 00:41:08.639
And someone on the outside
helped him.

316
00:41:08.640 --> 00:41:11.079
And I suppose you think
that someone was me?

317
00:41:11.080 --> 00:41:12.799
No.

318
00:41:12.800 --> 00:41:14.440
It was Cornelius.

319
00:41:17.160 --> 00:41:18.760
Elliot saw him. Marian.

320
00:41:19.440 --> 00:41:21.319
And the driver of
last night's shipment

321
00:41:21.320 --> 00:41:23.759
stopped off at Cornelius's fun fair.

322
00:41:23.760 --> 00:41:25.560
Your brother is back.

323
00:43:44.640 --> 00:43:46.240
Just here. Thank you so much.

324
00:44:10.640 --> 00:44:12.240
You look well.

325
00:44:14.400 --> 00:44:16.600
You think you're safe in there?

326
00:44:20.560 --> 00:44:21.879
You're not safe.

327
00:44:21.880 --> 00:44:24.599
What no. "Hello Sean.
how are you doing mate?"

328
00:44:24.600 --> 00:44:27.079
I'm gonna make you pay
for what you've done.

329
00:44:27.080 --> 00:44:29.759
Listen. I'd love to sit and chat.

330
00:44:29.760 --> 00:44:33.520
hear you talk shit. but I've got
a court appearance to get ready for.

331
00:44:34.240 --> 00:44:36.359
Done!

332
00:44:36.360 --> 00:44:38.000
Recognise him?

333
00:44:41.280 --> 00:44:42.760
Should I? Yeah.

334
00:44:43.800 --> 00:44:45.320
He helped you spike my drugs.

335
00:44:46.600 --> 00:44:48.239
You're losing it mate.

336
00:44:48.240 --> 00:44:50.520
The pressure's
getting to you. isn't it?

337
00:44:54.960 --> 00:44:56.800
My wife and son...

338
00:44:58.240 --> 00:45:01.159
were killed in a hit and run
seven years ago.

339
00:45:01.160 --> 00:45:03.880
The driver vanished.
not a fucking trace.

340
00:45:06.200 --> 00:45:07.919
Until he rocks up last night.

341
00:45:07.920 --> 00:45:10.360
kills my driver.
and three of Faz's men.

342
00:45:12.440 --> 00:45:15.320
That was your wife?
So you do know him?

343
00:45:16.040 --> 00:45:18.399
Did you fucking hire him? No.

344
00:45:18.400 --> 00:45:21.919
I recognise the face. that's all.

345
00:45:21.920 --> 00:45:23.600
Heard the chatter.

346
00:45:25.400 --> 00:45:27.000
He's a good bloke though.

347
00:45:28.360 --> 00:45:29.960
You think this is a joke?

348
00:45:30.800 --> 00:45:33.479
Hiring the hit and run driver
to spike those drugs?

349
00:45:33.480 --> 00:45:35.240
It wasn't a hit and run.

350
00:45:38.920 --> 00:45:41.240
Look. I heard...

351
00:45:41.920 --> 00:45:45.440
he was paid
to crash into your wife.

352
00:45:46.240 --> 00:45:47.840
It was a targeted kill.

353
00:45:49.200 --> 00:45:50.920
That's the story on the street.

354
00:45:53.400 --> 00:45:55.280
What you didn't know that?

355
00:45:58.200 --> 00:45:59.520
You're fucking lying!

356
00:46:00.840 --> 00:46:02.159
Yeah. Fucking lying!

357
00:46:02.160 --> 00:46:04.959
Wait. what... What's his name?

358
00:46:04.960 --> 00:46:07.239
Who-Who paid him to do that?
I've got to go. Elliot.

359
00:46:07.240 --> 00:46:09.680
No. fucking sit...
Sean. wait! Wait! Wait.

360
00:46:12.960 --> 00:46:14.400
Tell me his name.

361
00:46:16.400 --> 00:46:17.960
You want me to tell you...

362
00:46:19.160 --> 00:46:22.400
then beg. Beg me to tell you.

363
00:46:29.720 --> 00:46:31.600
Or don't. OK.

364
00:46:36.200 --> 00:46:37.800
OK.

365
00:46:40.520 --> 00:46:42.879
I am begging you. Sean.
What's his name?

366
00:46:42.880 --> 00:46:45.679
No. I-I mean properly beg.

367
00:46:45.680 --> 00:46:47.560
Like you mean it.

368
00:46:59.520 --> 00:47:01.120
Please.

369
00:47:03.120 --> 00:47:05.320
Please. Sean. tell me his name.

370
00:47:09.080 --> 00:47:10.519
Nah. I don't think so.

371
00:47:10.520 --> 00:47:11.679
Tell me!

372
00:47:11.680 --> 00:47:13.799
Goodbye. Elliot.
Sean. come back!

373
00:47:13.800 --> 00:47:16.399
Sean! Sean. come back here you worm!

374
00:47:16.400 --> 00:47:19.159
Hey. Calm down. Calm down.
Yeah. Yeah. Of course. Of course.

375
00:47:19.160 --> 00:47:21.919
Sean!
Tell me or I'll fucking kill you!

376
00:47:21.920 --> 00:47:23.919
That's it. Enough. Sean!

377
00:47:23.920 --> 00:47:27.480
Enough.

